Package org.cesecore.roles.member

Class RoleMemberData

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cesecore.dbprotection.ProtectedData
      • org.cesecore.roles.member.RoleMemberData
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<RoleMemberData>
    @Entity
public class RoleMemberData
extends ProtectedData
implements Serializable, Comparable<RoleMemberData>
    Entity bean for Role members. Does not correspond to a physical entity, but rather to an individual credential linked to an entity. The same individuals may share the same credential (such as belonging to the same organization, or sharing an account, while one individual may have access to several credentials (such as a user using several different certificates for identification depending on location). Each member is linked to a Role, though not intrinsically so via foreign keys
    Version:
    $Id: RoleMemberData.java 25634 2017-04-03 12:02:08Z jeklund $

      • RoleMemberData

        public RoleMemberData​(int primaryKey,
                      String tokenType,
                      int tokenIssuerId,
                      int tokenMatchKey,
                      int tokenMatchOperator,
                      String tokenMatchValue,
                      int roleId,
                      String description)
        Slightly more verbose constructor used for upgrades.
        Parameters:
        primaryKey - the primary key for this object. It's required to check the database for any objects with the same key, otherwise that object will be overridden
        tokenType - a string which defined the implementation of AcceessMatchValue used by this member
        tokenIssuerId - the issuer of token if relevant or 0 (RoleMember.NO_ISSUER) otherwise
        tokenMatchKey - the integer value determining how to interpret the tokenMatchValue, defined in a class that inherits the interface AcceessMatchValue
        tokenMatchOperator - how to perform the match. 0 (AccessMatchType.UNUSED.getNumericValue())to let the determine this from tokenSubType.
        tokenMatchValue - the actual value with which to match
        roleId - the ID of the role to which this member belongs. May be null.
        description - a human readable description of this role member. Null will be treated as an empty String.

      • getZzzRowProtection

        @Deprecated
public String getZzzRowProtection()
        Deprecated.
        Use getRowProtection() instead
        Horrible work-around due to the fact that Oracle needs to have (LONG and) CLOB values last in order to avoid ORA-24816. Since Hibernate sorts columns by the property names, naming this Z-something will apparently ensure that this column is used last.
        Returns:
        string

      • getProtectString

        protected String getProtectString​(int version)
        Description copied from class: ProtectedData
        asks the data class for the string to be protected. Version is -1 for a new row to be protected, and otherwise a version given earlier from the data class when storing the row.
        Specified by:
        getProtectString in class ProtectedData
        Parameters:
        version - the version of the string that is protected, used as input when verifying data. -1 when getting protection string for data to be inserted or updated. -1 means that the data class should use it's latest version of protect string
        Returns:
        String to be integrity protected, i.e. input to hmac.

      • getProtectVersion

        protected int getProtectVersion()
        Description copied from class: ProtectedData
        asks the data class for the version of the string that is protected, used as input to getProtectString() when verifying data. This is used so that the data class can alter itself with new fields, but still be backwards compatible and verify older database data. Called when getting the version for inserts or updates.
        Specified by:
        getProtectVersion in class ProtectedData
        Returns:
        int version the latest version of protection string.
